            <p>Light-duty monorail systems carry 100-500 lbs per carrier. Medium-duty power-and-free systems handle 500-2,000 lbs. Heavy-duty automotive systems carry 4,000-10,000 lbs per carrier , enough for complete car bodies with fixtures. The building structure must support the total suspended load of track, chain, carriers, and products.</p>
